This paper deals with data poisoning attacks in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves security and privacy concerns in machine learning, which could fall under the subfield of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper discusses the effectiveness of various defenses against data poisoning attacks, which could be relevant to the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper may involve computer vision (cs.CV) if the machine learning models being attacked and defended are used for image recognition tasks. Finally, the paper may involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) if it discusses the efficiency of different defense mechanisms.
